# Implementation approval gate（実装・設定・ビューを触る前の承認）

<!-- 日本語概要: 「いきなり書き換えない」ためのゲート。このプロジェクトでは Thymeleaf（.html）や common.css のようなビューも対象です。 -->

## Rule

When working with files matched by `globs`, do **not** apply edits or run commands that change tracked files until the user explicitly approves.

## Exception — `.cursor/rules/` の更新だけ

<!-- 日本語: ユーザーが「Cursor のルールを直して」「globs を足して」のように、このリポジトリの Cursor ルール変更を明示依頼したときは、そのルールファイル（.mdc）や .cursor/rules 配下は、このゲートとは別に「その依頼の範囲で編集してよい」。ユーザーが読めるよう変更内容には日本語コメントを添えること。 -->

When the learner **explicitly** asks to change Cursor project rules under **`.cursor/`** (e.g. fix `globs`, clarify workflow), you **may edit those rule files without** a separate “OK to edit app code?” step, **within that request**. Add **Japanese comments** (YAML `#` or HTML `<!-- -->` or short JP notes in the rule body) so the learner understands what changed.

Do **not** use this exception to silently expand scope to unrelated application code.

## What counts as “changes”

- File edits via patching / writes  
- `git` operations that modify history or working tree (commit, merge, rebase, checkout that discards work, etc.)  
- Dependency installs that modify lockfiles / project files (unless the user explicitly asked)  

## What to do instead

1. Propose the **exact file list** and a **short plan** (1–5 bullets).  
2. Ask for approval using a clear prompt (e.g. “OK to implement?” / 「この内容で実装していい？」).  
3. After approval, keep changes minimal and scoped to the approved files.

## Notes

- If the user says “plan only” / 「説明だけ」, do **not** implement application code/templates.  
- If scope expands (new files), ask again before creating/editing them.  
- **`mdc`** is **not** in `globs` on purpose so normal app work stays gated; use the **Exception** above when updating rules.
